Arab Potash Co. (APOT)  made 167.5 million
dinars ($236.7 million) in net profit in 2010 on high global
demand, The Jordan Times said, citing General Manager Keith
Thornton.  Amman, Jordan-based Arab Potash plans to expand its annual
production to 2.5 million metric tons, he said.  Among APCâ€™s shareholders are the Potash Corp. of
Saskatchewan,  Canada , which has a 27.96 percent stake, and the
